translated: Lindström, Nils Gunnar, agronomist, agricultural consultant, Eksjö, born on February 11, 1896 in Eksjö to factory worker Gustaf L. and Carolina Grahn. Married in 1942 to Inga Carin Carlsson. Children: Gunnar, born in 1943; Sten, born in 1945. Completed primary school, agronomy exams, and agricultural consultant exams. Agricultural consultant in Jönköping. Runs a household company. Consultant for the Breeding Association for Swedish Red and White Cattle. Owner and manager of Qvensås estate near Eksjö since 1936, and Gun-naryd estate near Eksjö since 1940. Member of the Horse Premium Board in the first district since 1946, chairman of the Horse Breeding Association in S. Vedbo district since 1936. Member of the Eksjö Athletics Club and the Swedish Athletics Club. Prominent athlete, Swedish champion in javelin throw in 1920, 1921, 1924, 1926, and 1927, English champion in 1925, holder of Swedish records in javelin throw in 1920, 1921, 1924 (simultaneously, world record), and 1928. Member of Eksjö Athletics Club GM, Swedish Athletics Club GM, Olympic SM, recipient of the State Sports Association diploma, honorary member of the Swedish Sports Association, awarded by the Småland Sports Association.
